&lt;li&gt;Conduct research, gather data, and synthesize findings to support strategic decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the creation, execution, and analysis of projects, campaigns, or product features&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with team members across Marketing, Sales, Product, Engineering, or Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help build, organize, and maintain internal tools, trackers, reports, or datasets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in team meetings and contribute ideas and recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of at least one project or deliverable over the course of the internship and present outcomes to the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned based on business needs and department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently pursuing a Bachelor&#39;s or Master&#39;s degree, or recently graduated (within the last 12 months)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any major considered; coursework or interest in Business, Marketing, Data Science, Computer Science, Life Sciences, Communications, or related fields is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized, detail-oriented, and able to manage multiple priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working independently and adapting quickly in a fast-paced startup environment&lt;/li&gt;
